kNN with NCCTG Lung Cancer Data

Source : https://vincentarelbundock.github.io/Rdatasets/doc/survival/cancer.html Description:

inst: Institution code time: Survival time in days status: censoring status 1=censored, 2=dead age: Age in years sex: Male=1 Female=2 ph.ecog: ECOG performance score (0=good 5=dead) ph.karno: Karnofsky performance score (bad=0-good=100) rated by physician pat.karno: Karnofsky performance score as rated by patient meal.cal: Calories consumed at meals wt.loss: Weight loss in last six months

Show Data:

cancer

Remove NA Values

clearedData <- cancer[complete.cases(cancer),]
# add target column
table(clearedData$status_result)
< table of extent 0 >
clearedData$status_result <- factor(clearedData$status, levels = c(1, 2), labels = c("censored", "dead"))

Normalize Data for PCA and kNN:

normalizedData <- scale(normalizedData[,2])

Fehler in normalizedData[, 2] : Indizierung außerhalb der Grenzen

PCA:

pca <- prcomp(normalizedData, center=TRUE, scale. = TRUE)
biplot(pca, cex=0.6, expand=1)

Split in Training and Testdata:

train_data <- normalizedData[1:55,]
test_data <- normalizedData[55:167,]
# labels
lbl_train_data <- ordinalValues[1:55]
lbl_test_data <- ordinalValues[55:167]
# installs
# install.packages("class")
# library(class)
predict <- knn(train = train_data, test=test_data, cl=lbl_train_data, k=10 )
# install.packages("gmodels")
# library(gmodels)
CrossTable(x = lbl_test_data, y = predict, prop.chisq = FALSE)
